        <heading>HISTORICAL AND STATUTORY NOTES</heading>
        <level>
          <heading>Miscellaneous Notes</heading>
          <text>Revision of chapter: D.C. Law 4-29 enacted the District of Columbia Uniform Controlled Substances Act of 1981. D.C. Law 4-29 repealed former §§ 33-501, 33-503 to 33-513, 33-515 to 33-520, 33-521(a), (c) through (g), and 33-522 to 33-526 [1981 Ed.], redesignated former §§ 33-502, 33-514, and 33-521 [1981 Ed.] as present §§ 48-921.01, 48-921.02, and 48-931.01, respectively, and enacted present §§ 48-901.02, 48-902.01 to 48-902.13, 48-903.01 to 48-903.09, 48-904.01 to 48-904.10, 48-905.01 to 48-905.07, and 48-906.01 to 48-906.03. Former § 33-509 [1981 Ed.] had been amended by D.C. Law 4-25.</text>
          <text>Former §§ 33-501 to 33-526 [1981 Ed.] as they existed prior to the revision of this chapter by D.C. Law 4-29, were part of the Uniform Narcotic Drug Act, approved June 20, 1938 (52 Stat. 785). D.C. Law 4-29 also repealed, inter alia, the provisions of former chapter 6 of this title, the Dangerous Drug Act for the District of Columbia, approved July 24, 1956 (70 Stat. 612).</text>
          <text>DC CODE D. VIII, T. 48, Subt. III, Ch. 9, Refs &amp; Annos</text>
